text: Roberta Parisella (born 26 August 1968) is an Italian taekwondo athlete. She competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the bantamweight event. At the European Taekwondo Championships she won the silver medal in 1986 and 1988. == References == Category:1968 births Category:Taekwondo practitioners Category:Olympians for Italy Category:Living people
